d by PostCommit). The commit diff itself tells us files were changed. The question is whether those changes existed before `UserPromptSubmit` or were introduced during the session. But at this point in PostCommit, the commit is already made — the files are in the commit. We can't distinguish pre-existing dirty state from agent-introduced changes just from the commit.\\n\\nHowever — we CAN check the pre-task file. That's a much cleaner signal:\\n\\n- **Pre-task file exists** → subagent is running → subagent likely made this commit → `hasNew = true`\\n- **No pre-task file** → no subagent → main agent or human made the commit → fall through to transcript check (which would succeed for main agent, or show no agent files for human)\\n\\nThis is more targeted than blindly trusting all ACTIVE sessions. What do you think?\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":1576,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":156058,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":1576},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CY9Exduva2mXwje6UNd8Q\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"ac677c82-a4ac-49e1-a9bb-12d92a5fbab1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-15T04:42:12.580Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ac677c82-a4ac-49e1-a9bb-12d92a5fbab1\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"e8811ad6-93d9-4ee6-997d-2447a5d496f3\",\"version\":\"2.1.42\",\"gitBranch\":\"alex/ent-297-fix-subagent-only-changes-checkpointing\",\"slug\":\"zippy-sparking-rocket\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"c3e46ff3-dd92-42a0-8068-7a7fd8eb7ec1\",\"toolUseID\":\"c3e46ff3-dd92-42a0-8068-7a7fd8eb7ec1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-15T04:42:12